HEADWORD: Dephlegmate
<hw>De*phleg"mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Dephlegmated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Dephlegmating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Dephlegm</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>To deprive of
superabundant water, as by evaporation or distillation; to clear of
aqueous matter; to rectify; -- used of spirits and acids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dephlegmation</ent>⟦br⟧
